---
<section data-test="problem-section" class="py-20 px-4 bg-[var(--card)]">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-4 text-[var(--fg)]">Why existing approaches fall short</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-[var(--muted)] mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Most teams ship code that diverges from their original intent — not because they're careless, but because there's no shared language between vision, spec, and implementation.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg)]">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">📋</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-[var(--fg)]">PRDs get stale</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">Product requirements docs are written once and forgotten. By sprint 3, nobody reads them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg)]">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🔀</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-[var(--fg)]">Stories drift from code</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">User stories live in Jira. Code lives in GitHub. They're never reconciled.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg)]">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🤖</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-[var(--fg)]">AI makes it worse</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--muted)]">Coding agents write what they infer, not what you meant. Without a spec, they hallucinate direction.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
